      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2024-08-13T17:03:42.421Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Yes, this delay and catch up process happens when phones reduce the power allocated to our app.  There might be an android setting to improve this but I have not heard of anyone with issues in a long time.  We occasionally see small catchups but seems pretty rare.</p>\n<p>Due to the technologies we use our app is pretty demanding and there is also no such thing as \u201cexact second timing\u201d so we have to deal with this.  In the past people used to see this on faster devices as well but we did a lot of performance improvements and this seems very rare now.  In your case I don\u2019t know if it is lots of background processes or what causes this.  Low battery for sure can cause this.</p>",
